00:11:49.843 --> 00:11:54.483
he had heard a group of men plotting in a pub about how they were

00:11:54.483 --> 00:11:59.253
going to set Doyle’s apartment on fire in a bid to intimidate him.

00:12:00.713 --> 00:12:06.593
This witness, William Love, was a petty criminal, and at the time that

00:12:06.603 --> 00:12:11.693
he gave this statement he was in jail awaiting trial for armed robbery.

00:12:13.133 --> 00:12:19.853
The names that he gave the police were Thomas “TC” Campbell and Joe Steele.

00:12:21.393 --> 00:12:26.903
Now, these men, TC Campbell and Joe Steele, were no angels.

00:12:27.993 --> 00:12:30.973
TC Campbell was well-known to the police.

00:12:31.613 --> 00:12:37.163
He also had an ice cream van, registered in his wife’s name, and there had been reports

00:12:37.163 --> 00:12:42.693
that he had been intimidating people for years, including other ice cream van drivers

00:12:42.883 --> 00:12:47.983
in a bid to protect his most profitable routes, from which he would sell stolen goods.

00:12:48.843 --> 00:12:50.783
He was arrested shortly afterwards.

00:12:51.943 --> 00:12:55.683
When the police searched his house, they reported that

00:12:55.683 --> 00:12:59.553
they found a street map with Doyle’s apartment circled out.

00:13:00.573 --> 00:13:05.183
The police also claimed that TC Campbell confessed his involvement,

00:13:05.583 --> 00:13:09.753
even though TC Campbell denies ever having made any such confession.

00:13:11.373 --> 00:13:17.353
The police also had another witness, another petty criminal who was in jail at the time.

00:13:18.443 --> 00:13:25.023
His name was Joseph Grainger, and he was willing to go on record saying that he was there at

00:13:25.023 --> 00:13:32.153
the scene of the crime, but it wasn’t him who lit the match: it was TC Campbell and Joe Steele.

00:13:33.363 --> 00:13:37.643
But TC Campbell and Joe Steele maintained their innocence.

00:13:38.573 --> 00:13:43.423
Sure, they might have done other things they regretted, but this wasn’t them.

00:13:43.753 --> 00:13:44.863
They were innocent.

00:13:46.363 --> 00:13:53.083
There was a trial, and the prosecution’s argument rested on four things: the testimony

00:13:53.233 --> 00:13:58.283
of the first petty criminal, William Love, who said that he had overheard a plot

00:13:58.483 --> 00:14:04.193
being made at a pub, the other petty criminal Joseph Grainger, who said that it was TC

00:14:04.193 --> 00:14:10.553
Campbell and Joe Steele, the map found in TC Campbell’s house, and the police statements.

00:14:12.133 --> 00:14:16.643
The problem was, when Joseph Grainger was questioned, he broke down.

00:14:17.243 --> 00:14:22.603
He admitted that he had made it up, he wasn’t there and had never said he was,

00:14:23.103 --> 00:14:27.563
but the police had pressured him into signing this statement because they had

00:14:27.593 --> 00:14:33.663
told him that if he collaborated he would get off the other, unrelated charges.

00:14:35.033 --> 00:14:38.993
And then there was the question of the map found at TC Campbell’s house.

00:14:40.363 --> 00:14:46.713
It seemed odd, unusual, for someone who was a career criminal to leave such

00:14:46.713 --> 00:14:51.103
an obviously incriminating piece of evidence visible to anyone who would come

00:14:51.103 --> 00:14:56.183
into the house, especially as, if he really did commit the crime, he would

00:14:56.183 --> 00:14:59.953
presumably have thought that the police might come knocking on his door.

00:15:01.213 --> 00:15:05.773
All throughout, he protested his innocence, saying that the map must have

00:15:05.773 --> 00:15:11.493
been planted by the police, placed there in a bid to frame him for the crime.

00:15:12.533 --> 00:15:17.363
Despite all of this, the jury was unanimous in its decision.

00:15:18.553 --> 00:15:24.793
The two men were guilty, and were each sentenced to life, at least 20 years in prison.

00:15:25.963 --> 00:15:30.333
The public was sick to death of the violence that had plagued the city,

00:15:30.633 --> 00:15:36.133
and horrified by the fact that an entire innocent law-abiding family,

00:15:36.533 --> 00:15:40.893
including an 18-month-old baby, had been murdered in their sleep.

00:15:42.263 --> 00:15:48.993
The jury no doubt saw these two men who were well-known violent criminals and thought, well,

00:15:49.373 --> 00:15:54.963
perhaps the evidence is a bit flimsy, but the city will be safer if they are behind bars.

00:15:56.163 --> 00:15:59.453
They were duly sent to prison, but constantly appealed.

00:15:59.683 --> 00:16:03.433
It wasn’t us, they said, you have the wrong people.

00:16:04.833 --> 00:16:08.893
Campbell went on hunger strike in a bid to try to get a retrial.

00:16:10.163 --> 00:16:13.663
Steele, on the other hand, had a different approach.

00:16:14.653 --> 00:16:18.053
He escaped from prison, doing so three times.

00:16:18.863 --> 00:16:23.253
And every time he escaped, he did some kind of publicity

00:16:23.253 --> 00:16:26.363
stunt to try to draw attention to his situation.

00:16:27.493 --> 00:16:32.103
The first time he climbed onto the roof of his mother’s house and shouted

00:16:32.113 --> 00:16:36.933
down his defence, but the following time he went one step further.

00:16:37.943 --> 00:16:43.463
He travelled to London, leaving Scotland for the first time in his life, and glued

00:16:43.673 --> 00:16:49.273
and handcuffed himself to the gates of Buckingham Palace, the royal residence,

00:16:49.493 --> 00:16:54.333
in a bid to speak to the journalists who descended to cover this unusual story.

00:16:55.363 --> 00:17:02.663
And it was…unusual, to go to all of the effort of escaping but to do something that would mean you

00:17:02.663 --> 00:17:08.553
would immediately be arrested, only to draw attention to the fact that you said you were innocent.

00:17:09.343 --> 00:17:12.883
It didn’t necessarily look like the actions of a guilty man.

00:17:13.933 --> 00:17:15.663
But it didn’t work.

00:17:16.353 --> 00:17:21.843
Steele was immediately put back in prison, and his request for an appeal denied.

00:17:23.263 --> 00:17:27.633
Fast forward a few years, and in 1992 there was a breakthrough.

00:17:28.913 --> 00:17:33.503
The case’s supposed “star witness”, William Love, admitted

00:17:33.513 --> 00:17:37.733
to journalists that he too had made the entire thing up.

00:17:38.593 --> 00:17:43.973
He said that police had encouraged him to testify against TC Campbell and Joe Steele, and

00:17:44.133 --> 00:17:49.003
he had gone along with it because he thought that they would let him off the other charges.

00:17:50.273 --> 00:17:54.133
But this was a private conversation between Love and

00:17:54.143 --> 00:17:57.863
journalists, it wasn’t evidence in a Scottish court of law.

00:17:59.103 --> 00:18:02.793
Still, it was a strong sign that the men were not

00:18:02.823 --> 00:18:06.333
guilty, or at least, that the case should be revisited.

00:18:07.283 --> 00:18:11.573
So, in 1996, pending the appeal, the two men were

00:18:11.573 --> 00:18:15.443
released on bail, 12 years after being sent to prison.

00:18:16.013 --> 00:18:17.823
They were free, finally.

00:18:19.083 --> 00:18:22.453
Two years later, they had their day in court, the case

00:18:22.453 --> 00:18:25.693
was duly referred to the Scottish Courts of Appeal.

00:18:26.915 --> 00:18:31.333
But, to their horror, their appeal was refused.

00:18:32.173 --> 00:18:36.913
Even though William Love had said that his testimony was a lie, meaning that

00:18:36.913 --> 00:18:41.163
there were now no witnesses putting them at the scene of the crime, there

00:18:41.163 --> 00:18:45.273
were still the statements from police officers saying that the two men had

00:18:45.273 --> 00:18:50.693
confessed, statements that the two men vehemently deny ever having made.

00:18:52.128 --> 00:18:57.068
Still the judge’s verdict stood; after living for two years as

00:18:57.068 --> 00:19:01.358
free men, TC Campbell and Joe Steele were sent back to prison.

00:19:02.888 --> 00:19:09.708
It wouldn’t be until 2004, 20 years after the crime, that the case was referred again,

00:19:10.278 --> 00:19:15.038
and a committee decided that the evidence of the police officers was not reliable.

00:19:16.308 --> 00:19:20.468
In other words, the police officers lied about Campbell and

00:19:20.468 --> 00:19:24.608
Steele’s confessions in a bid to frame them for the crime.

00:19:25.708 --> 00:19:31.608
The pair were officially declared innocent, and they were allowed to walk free after

00:19:31.608 --> 00:19:36.808
two decades of being thought of as the men who burned an innocent family to death.

00:19:37.858 --> 00:19:42.268
And the people who really committed the crime, if we are to presume

00:19:42.268 --> 00:19:46.878
that TC Campbell and Joe Steele are innocent, the guilty parties

00:19:47.078 --> 00:19:51.658
have never been found, nobody else has been convicted for the crime.

00:19:53.008 --> 00:19:58.423
In an interview from 2019, Joe Steele told a Scottish newspaper that it

00:19:58.428 --> 00:20:02.668
was another local criminal called Tam McGraw who was behind the murder.

00:20:03.978 --> 00:20:09.168
He was, according to Steele, a close friend of the police, and that’s why the

00:20:09.178 --> 00:20:13.798
law enforcement officers tried so hard to pin the crime on TC Campbell and Joe

00:20:13.798 --> 00:20:18.338
Steele, so that their friend and associate wouldn’t have to pay for what he did.

00:20:19.658 --> 00:20:24.718
Tam McGraw was asked about the murder, but he always denied it, and if

00:20:24.718 --> 00:20:29.928
it really was him, he took the truth to the grave, as he died in 2007.

